{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2018-04-26---react-fragment/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"waiyan.yoon"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"6a57db39-ade1-5901-9dbc-cf97206b5383","excerpt":"React developers know what does it mean when they saw this error: Adjacent JSX elements must be wrapped in an enclosing tag It’s simply fixed by adding  tags…","html":"<p>React developers know what does it mean when they saw this error:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Adjacent JSX elements must be wrapped in an enclosing tag</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It’s simply fixed by adding <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;div></code> tags between the element. At least it used to be, until I saw <code class=\"language-text\">React.Fragment</code> in a blog and read the new official documentation of React. It’s as simple as replacing <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;div></code> tag with <code class=\"language-text\">React.Fragment</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Fragment <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">MyFragment</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Fragment<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>First div<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Second div<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Fragment<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> MyFragment<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The use of <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Fragment></code> will not render extra <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;div></code> tag, which is a good news in certain case of styling.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Use of React.Fragment","date":"April 26, 2018","description":"","tags":["react","javascript"]}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-04-25---deploying-rails-5-2-applications-with-encrypted-credentials-using-capistrano/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Deploying Rails 5.2 Applications with New Encrypted Credentials using Capistrano"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-04-27---the-art-of-finding-a-lost-rubygem/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The Art of Finding a Lost Ruby Gem"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"6a57db39-ade1-5901-9dbc-cf97206b5383","previousPostId":"5484272c-9c11-53ee-a053-0fd3664f2e60","nextPostId":"19e6a358-d907-5c1d-8170-66b57e5796ad"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","3257411868"]}